[URL='http://forums.bukkit.org/threads/admn-info-permissions-v2-0-revolutionizing-the-group-system.1403/'][B]Permissions Required [/B][/URL]
[URL='http://forums.bukkit.org/threads/admn-info-permissions-v2-0-revolutionizing-the-group-system.1403/'][/URL]Since the Permissions dl's are down here's my latest build of their github repository [URL='http://dl.dropbox.com/u/4299882/Minecraft/InventorySort/1.5/Permissions.jar']Permissions 2.1 [/URL]this has no changes made by me in it.

InventorySort also works with Permissions 2.0

InventorySort allows you to sort all or part of your inventory ordered on the block/item TypeId number. You can also sort chests in the same manner.

[B]Commands:[/B]
[LIST]
[*][B]/sort all - [/B]Sorts all of the slots in your inventory(slots 0-35)
[*][B]/sort top - [/B]Sorts the "Backpack" slots of your inventory(slots 9-35)
[*][B]/sort 4 35 -[/B] Sorts slots 4-35
[*][B]/sort 30 10 - [/B]Sorts slots 10-35
[*][B]/sortchest - [/B]Sorts all of the slots in a chest or doublechest (alias: [B]/srtc[/B])
[*][B]/sort stack - [/B]Toggles whether sorting stack's first (default off) will remember between sessions as long as the server hasn't been restarted.
[/LIST]
[B]Permissions:[/B]
[CODE]iSort.basic.all - /sort all command
iSort.basic.top - /sort top command
iSort.basic.range - /sort [0-35] [0-35] command
iSort.basic.chest - /sortchest command
iSort.adv.stack - /sort stack command[/CODE]

[B]Side Note/Thanks:[/B]

The plugin Stacks items first then sorts them. This is based from the stack command in [URL='http://forums.bukkit.org/threads/sec-worldguard-v3-2-2-protect-areas-block-fire-info-about-4-x-available.790/']WorldGuard[/URL][B]. [/B]This also used the ItemType.java from it.

To get the chest your looking at I'm using TargetBlock.java from the [URL='http://forums.bukkit.org/threads/mech-mysignedit-v1-2.1436/']MySignEdit[/URL] plugin[B].[/B]

I love open-source[B]![/B]

